    <span>A. Choose the words for the following meanings.</span>
    <br>
    <br>
    <span>a. the severely damaging or destructive effects of something</span>
    <br>
    ravage
    <br>
    <br>
    <span>b. someone forced to leave their country in order to escape war, persecution, or natural disaster</span>
    <br>
    refugee
    <br>
    <br>
    <span>c. to face a difficult situation</span>
    <br>
    confront
    <br>
    <br>
    <span>d. take a position of power or importance illegally or by force</span>
    <br>
    usurp
    <br>
    <br>
