    <span>C. Fill in the gaps with the correct word from the brackets.</span>
    <br>
    <br>
    a. I asked him if he was attending the ceremony and he <b><u>shook</u></b> his head 'no'. <i>(shook/moved/
        nodded)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    b. They made a horrible decision which caused <b><u>irreparable</u></b> damage to our company.
    <i>(hopeless/inflexible/irreparable)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    c. The leaders need to break down <b><u>barriers</u></b> so as to create favorable environment in the nation.
    <i>(barriers/obstacles/hindrances)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    d. You ought to talk to the manager to <b><u>settle</u></b> the dispute. <i>(solve/settle/clear up)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    e. Perhaps this issue will not get much media <b><u>coverage</u></b>. <i>(security/examination/ coverage)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    f. This week is the first week of Joan as an in-charge. Everything is running <b><u>smoothly</u></b>.
    <i>(smoothly/calmly/easily)</i>
    <br>
    <br>
    g. I haven't read the text thoroughly, but given a <b><u>quick</u></b> glance. <i>(fast/quick/rapid)</i>
